// =============================================================================
// core/concurrency/mod.vr — Stdlib surface for typed concurrency models
// =============================================================================
// Layer: Standard Library / Concurrency
// =============================================================================
//
// Higher-level concurrency primitives that go beyond the plain
// `core.async` / `core.sync` layer — these are TYPED concurrency
// models where the type system enforces the protocol shape:
//
//   * `process.vr` — Process-calculus-style concurrent primitives.
//     Aligns with the Hoare-CSP / π-calculus tradition: processes
//     interact through typed channels, with the type system
//     tracking the protocol grammar.
//
//   * `session.vr` — Session-typed channel protocols (Honda-
//     Vasconcelos-Kubo 1998). Linearly-tracked channels carrying
//     a type-level session-protocol grammar (`Send<T>; Recv<U>;
//     End`). Misuse (skipping a step, double-receive) is a
//     type-error rather than a runtime deadlock.
//
// Distinct from `core.async` (Future/Task/Channel without
// type-level protocols) and `core.sync` (Mutex/RwLock/atomics —
// shared-memory concurrency primitives).
// =============================================================================

module core.concurrency;

public module process;
public module session;
